    {
      "instruction": "<p>Stir through the<strong> drained lentils</strong>,<strong> grated Italian hard cheese</strong>, <strong>panko breadcrumbs, </strong>juice of the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Divide the<strong> mixture</strong> into 8 <span class=\"text-danger\">[16]</span> and shape into <strong>balls </strong>(clean hands is the best way!) – these are your <strong>lemony aubergine balls</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>lemony aubergine balls</strong> to a<strong> </strong>baking tray (drizzle the tray with <strong>olive oil</strong> to avoid sticking!) and put it in the oven to cook for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
